\begin{theorem}
Let $R$ be a ring with unity, and let $M$ be a free $R$-module of finite dimension $n>0$. If $\mathcal A$, $\mathcal B$, and $\mathcal C$ are ordered bases of $M$, and $\mathbf M_{\mathcal A,\mathcal B}$, $\mathbf M_{\mathcal B,\mathcal C}$, and $\mathbf M_{\mathcal A,\mathcal C}$ denote the change of basis matrices from $\mathcal A$ to $\mathcal B$, $\mathcal B$ to $\mathcal C$, and $\mathcal A$ to $\mathcal C$ respectively, then $\mathbf M_{\mathcal A,\mathcal C} = \mathbf M_{\mathcal A,\mathcal B} \cdot \mathbf M_{\mathcal B,\mathcal C}$.
