Let $f(n)$ and $g(n)$ be arbitrary arithmetic functions. Consider the sequences $\langle a_n \rangle$, $\langle b_n \rangle$, and $\langle c_n \rangle$ defined for $n \ge 0$ by the following recurrence relations:
\begin{align*}
a_n &= \begin{cases}
0 & \text{if } n = 0 \\
1 & \text{if } n = 1 \\
a_{n - 1} + a_{n - 2} + f(n - 2) & \text{if } n > 1
\end{cases} \\
b_n &= \begin{cases}
0 & \text{if } n = 0 \\
1 & \text{if } n = 1 \\
b_{n - 1} + b_{n - 2} + g(n - 2) & \text{if } n > 1
\end{cases} \\
c_n &= \begin{cases}
