for arbitrary constants $x$ and $y$. If $F_n$ denotes the $n$-th Fibonacci number with $F_0=0$ and $F_1=1$, then $c_n$ can be expressed as $c_n = x a_n + y b_n + (1 - x - y) F_n$.

Let $T$ be a topological space and $H \subseteq T$. If $H^-$ denotes the closure of $H$, $H^\circ$ denotes the interior of $H$, and $\complement H$ denotes the complement of $H$ in $T$ (i.e., $\complement H = T \setminus H$), then the following identities hold:
\begin{align*}
\complement (H^\circ) &= (\complement H)^- \\
(\complement H)^\circ &= \complement (H^-)
\end{align*}
Equivalently, these can be expressed as:
\begin{align*}
T \setminus H^\circ &= (T \setminus H)^- \\
(T \setminus H)^\circ &= T \setminus H^-
\end{align*}

