Theorem: Multiplication modulo $m$ is distributive over addition modulo $m$.
Specifically, for any equivalence classes $[x]_m, [y]_m, [z]_m \in \mathbb{Z}_m$, the following properties hold:
\begin{align*}
[x]_m \cdot ([y]_m + [z]_m) &= ([x]_m \cdot [y]_m) + ([x]_m \cdot [z]_m) \\
([x]_m + [y]_m) \cdot [z]_m &= ([x]_m \cdot [z]_m) + ([y]_m \cdot [z]_m)
\end{align*}
where $\mathbb{Z}_m$ is the set of integers modulo $m$.
